 identify who they think people were coming to for solutions, or someone everyone knew. “I can imagine how many people they actually picked up and no one knows about till today. I have become paranoid and suspicious of everyone around me. Such a nightmare. This isn’t a country “And to top it all “I AM POOR” I’ve joked around with this sentence lately with my friends but it’s not funny. Imagine not being able to access the money you worked for Woman shrugging who does that? Should I be begging to feed?” Just so you know not only did they block my account. I was arrested, beaten, threatened. They promised to throw me in a canal where no one will ever find me. said they wouldn’t take me to any police station because they know we have people who would come and bail me #EndSARS pic.twitter.com/Q5RrDGcKeT — Temilola. O #endsars (@dhammythemmy) December 4, 2020  Meanwhile, there might be a second wave of the #EndSARS protest as concerned Nigerian youths have again started trending the hashtag #EndSARS on Twitter, calling on the Inspector General of Police to put an end to police brutality, and also bring to Justice, the hoodlums who attacked peaceful #EndSARS protesters. Here are some posts shared on Twitter: @vhic_tore “The I.G.P is yet to find this dangerous man but the only thing he’s concerned about is a Judicial panel without machetes and guns. #EndSARS” @tiana_okposin “A good day to soro soke on the #endsars matter! My fellow online protesters are you ready??? RT like crazyy!!” @J_mathofficial “Online protesters you have only one job, retweet aggressively……. just retweet, keep retweeting #EndSARS” Good morning sir, @jidesanwoolu , when will you arrest this guy and his cohorts?#EndSARS pic.twitter.com/0lGaE51fNR — Young Oche (@youngoche) December 4, 2020  When will this monster be arrested? @jidesanwoolu #EndSARS pic.twitter.com/PCApnZ4Ro3 — SavvyRinu’s BF#SarsMustEND (@OmoBabaPastor44) December 4, 2020  Don’t be silent. Be like the mosquito in your rooms… No matter how many you kill they always come back to get what they want. With one buzz we move #EndSARS pic.twitter.com/0Y43afWLux — Killianfrancis (@killianfran6) December 4, 2020  Vanguard News Nigeria By Emmanuel Okogba A doctor by the name Temilola Balogun who assisted protesters during the #EndSARS campaign and was arrested has recounted what she passed through in the hand of the police. Dr Balogun's arrest was made known on the 20th of October by another Twitter user by the name… December 4, 2020 In "News" When the social media hashtag #EndSARS campaign moved from the street of twitter into a full-fledged live protest on October 8, as a writer, I decided to document my thought process. October 22, 2020 In "Viewpoint" …How Police deceived me to arrest my brother, Eromosele Adene, in Lagos – Sister …Says brother has liver problems, begs for his release …My client moved to Abuja, denied bail, police playing hide-and-seek, says Lawyer …Police deny arresting protesters •We will meet in court- Dr Pam Pam …Stop harassing innocent… November 11, 2020 In "News"